[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hackney police officer shooting: Man appears in court

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man accused of attempting to murder a policeman who was shot during an undercover operation has appeared in court.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Tyrone Henry, 31, of Phoenix Close, Hackney, is also charged with possession of a firearm with intent to endanger life and illegally possessing a firearm.
He confirmed his name, address and date of birth during the hearing at Thames Magistrates' Court in Bow.
The detective is in a stable condition.
He was shot in the shoulder on Thursday afternoon in Haggerston
Mr Henry was told by District Judge Mary Connolly he will next appear at Wood Green Crown Court on October 29.
